.Dd March 31, 2026
.Dt MANEATER 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm maneater
.Nd man page MCP server with semantic search
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Cm serve mcp
.Nm
.Cm index
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is an MCP (Model Context Protocol) server that provides Unix man page
documentation with progressive disclosure and embedding-based semantic search.
It runs as a child server behind
.Xr moxy 1 .
.Pp
The following commands are available:
.Bl -tag -width "serve mcp"
.It Cm serve mcp
Run as an MCP server over stdio.
Exposes man pages as resources using the following URI templates:
.Bl -tag -width "man://search/{query}" -compact
.It man://{page}
Table of contents with section names and line counts.
.It man://{page}/{section_name}
Read a specific section of a man page.
.It man://{section}/{page}
Table of contents for a specific man section number.
.It man://search/{query}
Semantic search for man pages by natural language query.
Accepts an optional
.Ar top_k
query parameter (default 10).
.El
.Pp
The search index is built lazily on the first search request if no
cached index exists.
.Pp
An
.Cm exec
tool is also available for running shell commands.
By default, no commands are permitted; allow rules must be configured in
.Xr maneater.toml 5
before any command will execute.
.It Cm index
Build or rebuild the search index with progress output to stdout.
The index is saved to the cache directory (see
.Sx FILES )
and reused by subsequent
.Cm serve mcp
sessions.
.El
.Pp
Bare invocation with no command prints usage and exits with status 1.
.Sh SETUP
.Ss Nix (recommended)
Install via the flake:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
nix build github:amarbel-llc/moxy#maneater
.Ed
.Pp
The Nix wrapper bundles all dependencies
.Pq mandoc, pandoc, tldr
and sets
.Ev MANEATER_MODEL_PATH
to the embedding model automatically.
.Ss Moxyfile configuration
Add to a moxyfile to run as a child server behind
.Xr moxy 1 :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[servers]]
name = "man"
command = "maneater serve mcp"
generate-resource-tools = true
.Ed
.Ss Pre-building the search index
The search index is built lazily on first query, but this takes several
minutes.
To build it ahead of time:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
maneater index
.Ed
.Pp
The tldr cache is populated automatically on the first index build
if it does not already exist.
.Ss Without Nix
Manually install the following dependencies:
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
.Xr mandoc 1
.It
.Xr pandoc 1
.It
.Xr tldr 1
.It
llama-cpp (linked at build time via pkg-config)
.El
.Pp
Download the nomic-embed-text-v1.5 Q8_0 GGUF model and set:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
export MANEATER_MODEL_PATH=/path/to/nomic-embed-text-v1.5.Q8_0.gguf
.Ed
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width "MANEATER_MODEL_PATH"
.It Ev MANPATH
Colon-separated list of directories to search for man pages.
.Nm
delegates to
.Xr manpath 1
to resolve this; if unset,
.Xr manpath 1
falls back to platform defaults.
.Pp
In addition to the system manpath,
.Nm
automatically probes the current working directory for
.Pa man/ ,
.Pa doc/man/ ,
and
.Pa share/man/
subdirectories.
These heuristic paths are prepended to the system manpath so
project-local man pages shadow system pages.
This behavior can be disabled or extended via the
.Va manpath
section in
.Xr maneater.toml 5 .
.It Ev MANEATER_MODEL_PATH
Path to the nomic-embed-text-v1.5 GGUF model file.
Required for semantic search.
Set automatically by the Nix wrapper.
.It Ev XDG_CACHE_HOME
Base directory for the search index cache.
Defaults to
.Pa ~/.cache .
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "$XDG_CACHE_HOME/maneater/man-index/"
.It Pa $XDG_CACHE_HOME/maneater/man-index/
Cached search index.
Contains
.Pa pages.txt
and
.Pa embeddings.jsonl .
Safe to delete; will be rebuilt on next search or
.Cm index
invocation.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr maneater.toml 5 ,
.Xr mandoc 1 ,
.Xr moxy 1 ,
.Xr moxy-native 7 ,
.Xr pandoc 1 ,
.Xr tldr 1
